  <summary>11/20/1995--Introduced.
Religious Symbols Fairness Act of 1995 - Declares that a private person shall have the right to place symbols (including religious symbols) meaningful to that person on public space, including government buildings, to the extent that the authority controlling the space allows all private persons the same right.</summary>
